        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 2:47PM EDT by NWS Burlington VT</headline>
        <description>At 247 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Clifton, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tupper Lake Village, Clifton, Colton, Tupper Lake, Piercefield, Fine,
Hopkinton, Clare, Parishville, Carry Falls Reservoir, Conifer,
Wanakena, Gale, Cranberry Lake, Newton Falls, Childwold, Star Lake,
and Shurtleff.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
